                <h1>Discovering Woodrow Wilson: A Legacy of Leadership</h1>
                <p>Woodrow Wilson was the 28th President of the United States, serving from 1913 to 1921. A member of the Democratic Party, he led the nation through World War I and was instrumental in the establishment of the League of Nations. His progressive reforms include the Federal Reserve Act and antitrust legislation, shaping modern American governance.</p>
